{id:"spell-spike-growth",name:"Spike Growth",content:[{id:"Title",content:"Spike Growth"},{id:"StatGrid",content:[{title:"Level",content:"2"},{title:"Casting Time",content:"1 action"},{title:"Range",content:"150 feet (20ft cylinder)"},{title:"Components",content:"V, S, M"},{title:"Duration",content:"Up to 10 minutes"},{title:"School",content:"Transmutation"}]},{id:"Subtitle",content:"Effect"},{id:"MultiText",content:["The ground in a 20-foot radius centered on a point within range twists and sprouts hard spikes and thorns. The area becomes difficult terrain for the duration. When a creature moves into or within the area, it takes 2d4 piercing damage for every 5 feet it travels.","The transformation of the ground is camouflaged to look natural. Any creature that can't see the area at the time the spell is cast can make a Wisdom (Perception) check against your spell save DC to recognize the terrain as hazardous before entering it."]}]}